02/04/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Slovenian Prime Minister Borut Pahor confirmed Thursday (April 1st) that Slovenia has no further need to block the foreign, security and defence policy negotiation chapter in accession talks with Croatia, Pahor said the Croatian-Slovenian commission has made progress on remaining issues between the two neighbours, but did not elaborate.
After meeting with Croatian PM Jadranka Kosor, Pahor voiced hope that the government and parliament will green-light the opening of this negotiation chapter.
Kosor wants to wrap up accession talks this year.
(Nova TV, HINA - 01/04/10;
HRT - 31/03/10)
